&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;The Royal Orthopaedic Hospital NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;JOB TITLE:                 Consultant in Spinal Surgery&lt;span&gt;            &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;HOURS:                     10 P.A. per week plus on call commitment &lt;br /&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ref:                             303-4013-1020-D1                             &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Royal Orthopaedic Hospital NHS Foundation Trust invites applications from orthopaedic surgeons or neurosurgeons to the position of consultant spinal surgeon.  This is a post required to ensure the Trust can continue to provide high quality and timely care for its patients, offering a comprehensive range of spinal surgery.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is an outstanding opportunity for a surgeon wishing to pursue a career dedicated to spinal surgery within an internationally renowned centre.  The department is recognized as a super-regional centre for spinal deformity and oncology, in particular for primary spinal tumours, as well as undertaking reconstructive surgery for infection and trauma along with the full range of degenerative conditions.  There is the opportunity for further subspecialisation within spinal surgery, to complement those within the department.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post is expected to attract 10 PA’s with an on-call commitment of approximately 1:10 providing emergency routine spinal care to Birmingham and Worcestershire, and beyond supported by 24/7 MRI access on site.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will have completed orthopaedic or neurosurgical training and hold FRCS(Orth) or FRCS(SN), be entered on the Specialist Register or within 3 months of this and have successfully completed a recognized spinal fellowship. They will hold a logbook and a working knowledge of spinal instruments commensurate with that.  Clear evidence of longstanding commitment to a career in spinal surgery is mandatory.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt; The post requires the appointee to work well within a team, demonstrating flexibility and team working and ensuring effective delivery of service and utilization of resource whilst maintaining high levels of patient care.  There are excellent opportunities to engage in audit and research.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note a DBS certificate is required for this post.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;br /&gt; For further information please contact Mr Andrew Young, Consultant Spinal Surgeon and Clinical Director, on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Andrew.young10@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; or 0121 685 4113.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
